<font color="#FF0000">MEMORIAL DAY BARBECUES</font><br>
<tt>Mon Jun  2 23:39:44 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
<br>
If I fail to formally mourn for fallen soldiers on Memorial Day, it is more a reflection of my weary condition from seldom having a day pass without black thoughts and faces of remembered dead.  The dour fear and feared betrayal is , that having survived being wasted in a war, I survived only to be &quot;wasted&quot; by car notes, a long-awaited vacation, and perhaps a nicer house in the country. I have yet to put any bricks in the promised wall of &quot;never again.&quot; I'm not sure how to begin.
<p><code>-- spurgeon@kode.net  (William Donald) </code><p>


